phrases: Looks like we are in the Zuland Plains.
Um, we should see it soon.
It is the spirit mountain of Fuji!
There is something over there that looks like a cow!
Ah, I think that is a green elk herd.
There is some distance between us, and they are said to be calm.
They really look just like cows.
I have heard they are delicious.
The path here seems to be curving a little.
There is so much grass, I cannot see the ocean at all.
But you can kind of smell the salt air, cannot you?
Hey, did not Shiroe say this road was...
That is what this used to be called.
It was one of the Five Routes.
It began in Nihonbashi, Tokyo, and it became an important trade route.
Today, the East Sea Road is called National Route 1,
and many roads branch off of it.
If you follow it all the way, it will take you to Osaka.
So the roads are connected in this world, too.
This might be the fastest route to the Redstone Mountains.
I have never really thought about the roads that way before.
While I am here, I am going to have an adventure, and learn all kinds of things!
Think it is about time for lunch?
The chief's ham sandwiches are so good!
Let us have Danish and Croissant work a little harder.
The path opens before Rundel Haus Code!
Okay, let us get going before it gets dark!
For the Twin Horse Flute of Lyman!
It was six hours a day, was not it?
Why did not anyone realize that, anyway?
Still, just because the time limit ran out,
they did not have to run away so fast.
They ate carrots out of my hand.
They really have no sense of human gratitude!
Then would they have horse gratitude, rather than human gratitude?
The horses ran off, but this is kind of nice.
Somewhere between the Kalbe Inn and Wilistoria Village.
Without them, we cannot go on...
Yeah, we will just have to do it.
This is where an adventurer really shines.
Being an adventurer has nothing to do with this.
When I am with Nyanta, I can make it just fine...
You just have not practiced enough.
The chief would say, You simply need to improve, little by little.
I wish we had a cooking skill.
Sorry to keep relying on you, Serara!
I need to keep a hold of myself.
I have got the Newlywed's Apron Dress, after all!
I need to do my best for Nyanta and for everyone else!
Looks like the next place we can stop is the town of Sazan.
How long will it take to get there?
If we can only use the horses for six hours a day,
it could take about three days.
Why is this road so twisty?
I wish it would just go straight.
Yeah, but as long as I get to travel with everyone like this,
I do not care if it takes a long time.
I think Shiroe and the others sent us on this trip to teach us this stuff.
I feel like you have really grown up from the person you used to be.
I thought I would grown up with you, but I guess I have a long way to go.
I can do my best because you have always been with me since I came to this world.
Well, I am your big brother.
It is been three days since they left on their trip.
I hope they are not getting homesick.
I am sure they are having a great time, like it is a field trip.
They may be saying they do not want to come back.
That would be a problem in itself.
You look just like my lord.
Is it hard without the scary glasses guy?
I realized how much I depended upon my lord.
For the moment, D.D.D. is stable,
but we do not know what will happen in the future.
I am sure I am causing a lot of problems for people,
and I will probably because more.
You do not need to worry about it.
My lord will not think of it as a bother.
He will help you of his own free will.
You do not need to worry about us now!
Is not that what being friends is?
If we were in the old world, I am sure we never could have been friends.
It is said that the cute are drawn to one another!
I would have met you two, no matter what!
Henrietta, stop rubbing your cheek against mine!
We did not need that kind of assurance!
Is that a Teaching for a ninja body-swapping technique?
That is the town of Sazan!
Our musician says she would like to play here tonight.
We will not because any trouble, so can you provide a place to perform?
I do not need any payment!
If you will just let me play here, that is enough.
We get to perform, and we can stay free for the night!
This is what I am capable of.
You guys perform to your hearts' content.
I really have learned a lot on this journey.
Even about the road we took to get here...
I wondered why there were so many twists and turns.
But when I traveled it on a carriage,
I saw that there were forests and hills,
so we could not just go straight.
The road goes around all those things to make it easier for people and carriages.
And this town was born so that, when you started to feel tired, you could rest.
Do not be afraid of the boredom.
When I was not able to play soccer with everyone,
I could not just watch with an expression like that.
Will my twisty path culminate in a city somewhere?
The customers kept asking for another song.
The encore calls would not stop.
They have a lot of energy.
I wonder what they are talking about.
I am not such a boor as to be interested in a secret chat among ladies.
I am simply impressed that they never run out of things to discuss.
That is because they are girls.
Then is the reason that Miss Isuzu is so pure and innocent because she is a lady?
She always wants to hug me and rub my hair!
I think she is just treating you like a dog.
Miss Isuzu does not act that way toward you.
Does she simply not think I am important?
I think it might mean you are special.
You are my doggy, so you are special.
When Isuzu thinks it is fun to be with you,
But I think that is different from being especially beautiful,
What does she think about me?
If thinking about it will not help,
I will get some sleep, too.
Today, we are going to cross into the Sakawa region.
In the modern world, that is Odawara.
They are famous for their fish paste.
We are going to follow this road to the ruined castle of Ariba.
To get to our goal, the Redstone Mountains,
we will either go off the Sea Road past the Ariba ruins and onto a smaller road,
or take a route that involves climbing mountains.
Since this area is a rice paddy zone, there are nature-type monsters.
Wild dogs, boars, and plant monsters live in the forests and mountains,
And Shiroe said the monsters along the road have their levels kept way down.
Then, even if we do run into one, we will be fine.
Sorry to have you take charge.
Isaac's actually looking forward to it.
Do not talk like you know me.
Anyway, so we have to train all the knights.
How many levels should we raise them?
Part of this is to forge friendships,
so two or three is fine.
They are People of the Land.
We cannot be reckless with them.
If we take the lead and fight high-level monsters,
the lower-level guys will rise in level automatically.
Their levels will go up, but they will not get stronger.
We can just alternate between power-leveling and combat training.
No, I will even focus on training!
This is starting to sound really macho,
but I guess it is okay.
Um, you still cannot reach Crusty?
He is not responding on his Friend List, either.
What is he doing that is so important, he would ignore his guild?
Lately, lots of people are leaving D.D.D.
Of course, it is actually surprising
the guild's managed to stay on course for these past three months.
He is either off playing somewhere or fighting.
I am worried about D.D.D., but...
The number of people in Honesty has exceeded 1,250.
This is above our previous record.
The majority of the new members are basically leechers.
They do not hunt or gather outside of Akihabara,
and they do not do crafting or trading in town, either.
These people like that are joining our guild and taking it easy.
People in Akihabara and the guild are getting angry with them.
It is only a matter of time before that rage explodes.
Of course, I have shared our opinion with the Round Table.
I think we simply have to kick them out.
Why not just limit who can join?
The only reason Honesty maintains its influence
and position on the Round Table
is because we are the third-largest guild in Akihabara.
If we lose that influence, we will lose our ability to influence Akihabara politics.
But I think it would be healthier if the guild...
No, the whole town of Akihabara went on a diet.
This will not be easy to cross.
Let us look for a way around.
They are being chased by ogres!
Get over there and keep them safe!
Do not let your guard down!
And there are fifteen of them!
Dark spirits have either evil poison,
or resistance to mind attacks and insta-kills.
Not only might we get hurt, but the People of the Land could, too!
I am not even touching them!
A traveling vampire, heading south, I suppose.
Roe 2 Race/ Half-Alv Summoner, Lv. 90 No Guild
Roe 2, a mysterious big sister who takes joy in being called big sister.
Tohya and the others enjoy their journey, even with the chaos she causes.
They encounter a group of adventurers who fight
to protect People of the Land from monsters.
I have friends to run with me.
